Simhasan (&quot;Throne&quot;) was a gem of a movie set in the seventies in Maharashtra, against the backdrop of a political struggle for Chief Ministership. The story is told through the eyes of a journalist who witnesses the now-cliche nexus between politicians and criminals. The black-and-white treatment made the realism even more believable. The dialog was also very realistic: famous line: aamchya maage adusashta ahet, adusashta -- sixty-eight!

Simhasan features some of the most accomplished actors of Marathi/Indian Cinema and theatre ever assembled.

Melodious Song :
Ushakaal Hota Hota Kaal Raatri Jhali, Arre Punha Aayushyanchya Petva Mashaali.

